elements.title: Isabel Coursier
elements.contents: ... that Isabel Coursier (pictured) was only 15 years old when she became the first North American to break the world record for women's ski jumping?

elements.title: Women's History Museum of Zambia
elements.contents: ... that Samba Yonga and Mulenga Kapwepwe founded the Women's History Museum of Zambia to counter a colonialist perspective on women's history?

elements.title: Barbara Neumann
elements.contents: ... that Barbara Neumann invented one of the first nanomaterials to be produced on an industrial scale?

elements.title: Breakfast
elements.contents: ... that the music video for "Breakfast" was reimagined by Dove Cameron after the Supreme Court of the United States' decision to overturn Roe v. Wade?

elements.title: Elena Gorolová
elements.contents: ... that Czech Romani social worker and human rights activist Elena Gorolová worked as a metalworker in her youth?

elements.title: Episode 8055
elements.contents: ... that Episode 8055 of the Australian television soap opera Neighbours is the first episode in the show's history to star and be directed and written entirely by women?

elements.title: Danielle Sassoon
elements.contents: ... that Danielle Sassoon, a former acting U.S. attorney for the Southern District of New York, credits her study of the Talmud for preparing her for her future legal career?

elements.title: Bibbidiba
elements.contents: ... that the ending of the music video for Hoshimachi Suisei's "Bibbidiba" was called inspiring to struggling women?

elements.title: Shirley A. Pomponi
elements.contents: ... that Shirley A. Pomponi helped to create a cancer drug out of a sea-sponge compound?
